u want to track <br />a file when it grows, for example. You'd just do something like<br /><br />	addr = mmap(... st.st_size ...)<br /><br />for the initial mapping, and then when the process notices that the file <br />has grown (or shrunk), it does a<br /><br />	mremap(addr, old_size, st.st_size)<br /><br />to be able to read the new pages.  A very logical interface, in fact.<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
